The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 23 May is 276,660 (31,886.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 18 May, there were 814 new confirmed cases (93.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 11 May, there were 912 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 11% (98 fewer cases).
